        ans.append(t[4])
        return
    if s > target:
        return
    for i in range(u, len(candidates)):
        c = candidates[i]
        t.append(c)
        dfs(s + c, i, t)
        t.pop()
ans = []
dfs(0, 0, [])
return ans
